TopicTitle: Hello and looking for some construction help!

Articles.Content:
Hello, I've played KSP for awhile now -- renewed interest in it lately and so I've decided to start a career (versus just playing sandbox).

I'm having problem with the construction of my rockets. I'm pretty early into this career and I have to go send a satellite to the Mun.

However, without SAS my rockets tend to tilt during flight, wobble, go all over the place and are generally uncontrollable. I have 135 hours+ logged and I am just now getting serious about career, so I know about radial, mirror, etc... attachment and I know about the offset and rotation tools.

This particular rocket I'm building now to complete the task is rotating towards 90 degrees and ends up in a spiral as I try to take control. I've done things like add In-Line Stabilizating Wheel but it doesn' fix the problem.

I was wondering if I could upload the ship and some more savvy players could tell me what is wrong with my construction; better yet, give me tips or at least point me in the right direction to where I can build great rockets and aircraft. At the present point, it is very frustrating.

The forum software doesn't have a file upload system, so I'll just put the .craft file in
